<subSubSection id="7BCE78F74BA8F036B227D5D642931B7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="FC4E891C3F1CC5D99B0670C70D3E888D" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="B8A2910312E045C842B42B439E13DBA4" LSID="http://zoobank.org/E87D3EDE-5038-439A-A904-7E0F87BB4546" authority="Evsyukov &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Zabiyaka &amp; Sadyrin, 2022" authorityName="Evsyukov &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Zabiyaka &amp; Sadyrin" authorityYear="2022" family="Julidae" genus="Bellatoiulus" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bellatoiulus" order="Julida" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Bellatoiulus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="64E40258494C8AD0672AE01F5F398768" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C936402042FE2E4118427DE63585FB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="type species">
<paragraph id="A2B32871B19430C7242269AAF49747E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E91E65F8B31F99EF3FBA74BAF4DBD6A" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="E413BD5CBFCBD603E37D62D063A13E99" authorityName="gen. et" authorityYear="2022" family="Julidae" genus="Bellatoiulus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bellatoiulus golovatchi" order="Julida" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="golovatchi">
<emphasis id="338E94C11F2041EC6712DA134557119F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Bellatoiulus golovatchi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. et sp. nov., by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81811581F36D3D4F267CB0D561B60698" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3E80C4E4C9E5E01F7C5710C1503DBE5C" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A95E046DB5E034C2375F320B5EACAACB" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
A genus of the julid tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4F50AEAB27A20564B5D394D14BCE4913" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1899" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" rank="tribe" tribe="Pachyiulini">Pachyiulini</taxonomicName>
, distinguished from all contribal genera by the unique presence of a lateral process on the opisthomere, as well as by the following combination of gonopodal and external somatic characters: promere with mesal ridge distally extending in a strong process, caudal face without apical denticles/ridges; opisthomere without anterior and caudal lamellae or these being vestigial, mesomeral process well-differentiated, crest-like, solenomere with a deep and narrow apical fovea; ommatidia absent, mandibular stipites in males not expanded, vertigial and metazonal setae present, pre-anal ring with an epiproct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55B499C447113A96DFC443548F5B04D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="name">
<paragraph id="FAD43AB86B04D4E948C3B441EBF425CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Name.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32DC82A56384693169E7DF2F0846C06C" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="3969A7F58718E18F7F81D6831CC39512" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">bellator</emphasis>
meaning 
<normalizedToken id="A1EF327EA516B8F7D5F5B2112C3A47D1" originalValue="“soldier”">&quot;soldier&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="905550090B1C3EBC2B00E64082D8D0BF" originalValue="“warrior”">&quot;warrior&quot;</normalizedToken>
, after the remarkably 
<normalizedToken id="A5A2D7A4F3796C3396CA5122E4910C22" originalValue="“armed”">&quot;armed&quot;</normalizedToken>
appearance of the gonopods including the club-like mesal and lateral processes of the promere and the opisthomere, respectively, and the apically serrated mesomeral process; plus 
<taxonomicName id="7E59851A0BFDB31C82DFA3E65C9766AF" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Julus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Julus" order="Julida" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D62B7E84B28CD981ABE56FBD8BDE28D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Julus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the type genus of the family 
<taxonomicName id="C8C7850D46E2508FC31B2864D6A9B947" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Julida" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Julidae</taxonomicName>
. Masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
